#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:4
msgid ""
"We’re pleased to announce the availability of Istio 0.3. Please see below"
" for what’s changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:7
msgid "{{< relnote >}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:10
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:12
msgid ""
"Starting with 0.3, Istio is switching to a monthly release cadence. We "
"hope this will help accelerate our ability to deliver timely "
"improvements. See `here </about/feature-stages/>`_ for information on the"
" state of individual features for this release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:17
msgid ""
"This is a fairly modest release in terms of new features as the team put "
"emphasis on internal infrastructure work to improve our velocity. Many "
"bugs and smaller issues have been addressed and overall performance has "
"been improved in a number of areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:23
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:25
msgid ""
"**Secure Control Plane Communication**. Mixer and Pilot are now secured "
"with mutual TLS, just like all services in a mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:28
msgid ""
"**Selective Authentication**. You can now control authentication on a "
"per-service basis via service annotations, which helps with incremental "
"migration to Istio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:33
msgid "Networking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:35
msgid ""
"**Egress rules for TCP**. You can now specify egress rules that affect "
"TCP-level traffic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:39
msgid "Policy enforcement and telemetry"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:41
msgid ""
"**Improved Caching**. Caching between Envoy and Mixer has gotten "
"substantially better, resulting in a significant drop in average latency "
"for authorization checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:45
msgid ""
"**Improved list Adapter**. The Mixer ‘list’ adapter now supports regular "
"expression matching. See the adapter’s `configuration options "
"</docs/reference/config/policy-and-telemetry/adapters/list/>`_ for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:50
msgid ""
"**Configuration Validation**. Mixer does more extensive validation of "
"configuration state in order to catch problems earlier. We expect to "
"invest more in this area in coming releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.3/index.rst:54
msgid ""
"If you’re into the nitty-gritty details, you can see our more detailed "
"low-level release notes `here "
"<https://github.com/istio/istio/wiki/v0.3.0>`_."
msgstr ""

